cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of surgical instrument segmentation in endoscopic vision, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks (DNN) and end-to-end training, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with robot-assisted surgery, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of novel Sinus-Surgery datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
